SIMPLE: filling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filling
<hw>Fill"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
which is used to fill a cavity or any empty space, or to supply a
deficiency; <as>as, <ex>filling</ex> for a cavity in a tooth, a
depression in a roadbed, the space between exterior and interior walls
of masonry, the pores of open-grained wood, the space between the outer
and inner planks of a vessel, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The woof in woven fabrics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Brewing)</fld> <def>Prepared wort added to ale to
cleanse it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Back filling</b></col>. <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Back</er>, <pos>a.</pos></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fillip</ent>⟦br⟧
